In this article, President Biden addresses the importance of artificial intelligence (AI) and the risks associated with it. He emphasizes the need to manage these risks to protect society, the economy, and national security. The administration is committed to safeguarding America's rights and safety by addressing privacy, bias, and disinformation in AI systems. President Biden mentions the proposed AI Bill of Rights, an executive order to root out bias in AI design, and a strategy for responsible AI development. He also highlights the harm that powerful technology can cause without proper safeguards, citing the need for bipartisan privacy legislation. The Vice President will convene civil rights leaders, consumer protection groups, and civil society to continue engagement on AI. President Biden expresses a desire to learn from and discuss AI with the experts present, requesting the press to leave the room. When asked about his son, Hunter Biden, he responds by saying he is proud of him.